# Technical Specifications

## Allowed Technologies and Libraries

The project strictly adheres to the following core technologies:

- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript
- One of the following CSS frameworks:
  - Bootstrap
  - Tailwind
  - Semantic UI
  - Foundation
- jQuery
- Flask (with plugins described in lectures)
- AJAX/Websockets
- SQLite interfaced via SQLAlchemy

## Restrictions

The following are not allowed:
- Other frameworks like React or Angular
- Other database systems like MySQL
- Advanced CSS preprocessors like SASS (when used directly)

## Exceptions

The following exceptions are permitted:
- JavaScript or Python libraries implementing non-core functionality specific to the application (e.g., ChatGPT bindings or graph visualization libraries)
- Font and icon libraries

## Code Conventions

- All code comments, content, and documentation must be in English
- Proper documentation is required for all modules
- Follow PEP 8 style guide for Python code

